  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h6869.html">H6869</a></span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H5337">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">הִצִּילָֽ/ם\׃</span>
  <span class="word-translit">hitziLa/m</span>
  <span class="word-english">he delivers/ them</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h5337.html">H5337</a></span>
</span></div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> The psalmist is using **hears** as a common expression of the culture to mean that Yahweh responds to them. If this does not have that meaning for your readers, you could use a comparable expression that does have that meaning or state the meaning plainly. Alternate translation: [and Yahweh pays attention to them]
    </div><div class="interlinear-verse hebrew-verse"><span class="verse-num">18</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H7138">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">קָר֣וֹב</span>
  <span class="word-translit">kaRov</span>
  <span class="word-english">is near</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h7138.html">H7138</a></span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H3068">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">יְ֭הוָה</span>
  <span class="word-translit">Yahweh</span>
  <span class="word-english">Yahweh</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h3068.html">H3068</a></span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H9005">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">לְ/נִשְׁבְּרֵי\־</span>
