  <span class="word-english">all</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h3605.html">H3605</a></span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H6106">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">עַצְמוֹתָ֑י/ו</span>
  <span class="word-translit">atzmoTa/v</span>
  <span class="word-english">bones/ his</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h6106.html">H6106</a></span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H259">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">אַחַ֥ת</span>
  <span class="word-translit">&#x27;aChat</span>
  <span class="word-english">one</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h259.html">H259</a></span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H9006">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">מֵ֝/הֵ֗נָּה</span>
  <span class="word-translit">me/Henah</span>
  <span class="word-english">from/ them</span>
  <span class="word-strongs">H9006</span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H3808">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">לֹ֣א</span>
  <span class="word-translit">lo&#x27;</span>
  <span class="word-english">not</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h3808.html">H3808</a></span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H7665">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">נִשְׁבָּֽרָה\׃</span>
  <span class="word-translit">nishBarah</span>
  <span class="word-english">it is broken</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h7665.html">H7665</a></span>
</span></div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> Here the psalmist uses part of a person **all his bones** to mean all of him and implies that Yahweh takes care of the entire person. If it would be helpful in your language, you could state the meaning plainly. Alternate translation: [He provides complete protection for him; he will not be harmed in any way]
    </div><div class="interlinear-verse hebrew-verse"><span class="verse-num">21</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H4191">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">תְּמוֹתֵ֣ת</span>
  <span class="word-translit">temoTet</span>
  <span class="word-english">it will kill</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h4191.html">H4191</a></span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H7563">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">רָשָׁ֣ע</span>
  <span class="word-translit">raSha&#x27;</span>
  <span class="word-english">the wicked</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h7563.html">H7563</a></span>
