  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h5650.html">H5650</a></span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H9002">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">וְ/לֹ֥א</span>
  <span class="word-translit">ve/Lo&#x27;</span>
  <span class="word-english">and/ not</span>
  <span class="word-strongs">H9002</span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H816">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">יֶ֝אְשְׁמ֗וּ</span>
  <span class="word-translit">ye&#x27;sheMu</span>
  <span class="word-english">they will be held guilty</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h816.html">H816</a></span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H3605">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">כָּֽל\־</span>
  <span class="word-translit">kal-</span>
  <span class="word-english">all</span>
  <span class="word-strongs"><a href="../lexicon/h3605.html">H3605</a></span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H9009">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">הַ/חֹסִ֥ים</span>
  <span class="word-translit">ha/choSim</span>
  <span class="word-english">those/ who take refuge</span>
  <span class="word-strongs">H9009</span>
</span><span class="interlinear-word" data-strongs="H9003">
  <span class="word-original hebrew">בּֽ/וֹ\׃</span>
  <span class="word-translit">b/o</span>
  <span class="word-english">in/ him</span>
  <span class="word-strongs">H9003</span>
</span></div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> The expression **will be condemned** is a passive verbal form. If your language does not use the passive form in this way, you can state this in active form or in another way that is natural in your language. It can also be stated in positive form. (See also: [[ Alternate translation: [Yahweh will forgive everyone who takes refuge in him]
    </div>
    <div class="tn-note">
      <strong>&#x1f4dd; Cultural Note:</strong> Here the psalmist speaks of going to Yahweh for protection as if he were a place where one can **take refuge**. You could use a comparable expression in your language or state the meaning plainly. Alternate translation: [who go to him for protection]
    </div>
